---
alwaysApply: true
---

Backend (NestJS):

- use modules per feature
- presentation / application / domain / infrastructure
- Prisma only in infrastructure
- avoid global services
- keep controllers thin

Unit tests:

- one spec file per module: `{module}.usecase.spec.ts` (e.g. `category.usecase.spec.ts`)
- all use cases in the module share a single `jest.Mocked<IRepository>` mock
- use `beforeEach(() => jest.clearAllMocks())` at the top level or per describe block
- instantiate use cases directly with `new UseCase(mockRepo)` — no NestJS testing module
- test descriptions in English